]).=C2=A0
It=E2=80=99s so much more deeply integrated throughout the financial rails =
that it can do things that competitors like Amex and Brex just can=E2=80=99=
t (or don=E2=80=99t), like:=C2=A0
Text a cardholder the second a transaction occurs to enter a receipt, up li=
mit via text, or anything else that a company might want to trigger =F0=9F=
=98=AF
Automatically match receipts in the moment or months later =F0=9F=98=AE
Categorize transactions based on data from the actual merchant, including w=
ild things like matching transactions to contractors based on their LinkedI=
n page=C2=A0 =F0=9F=98=B2
Approve or deny a transaction based on the company=E2=80=99s expense policy=
 at the point-of-sale, before it ever goes through =F0=9F=A4=AF
